    <item>
      <title>Token</title>
      <link>https://docs.hyperstable.xyz/docs/peg/token/</link>
      <pubDate>Sat, 07 Jun 2025 10:33:49 +0200</pubDate>
      <guid>https://docs.hyperstable.xyz/docs/peg/token/</guid>
      <description>&lt;p&gt;Hyperstable uses two tokens to manage its utility and governance:&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;ul&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;&lt;code&gt;PEG&lt;/code&gt; (ERC-20), is distributed to liquidity providers through emissions&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;&lt;code&gt;vePEG&lt;/code&gt; (ERC-721) which is used for governance, to vote on emissions, to earn (100% of) protocol revenue from interest and liquidation fees and receive incentives. &lt;code&gt;vePEG&lt;/code&gt; also gets protected from dilution via rebases.  &lt;code&gt;vePEG&lt;/code&gt; is represented as a (transferrable) NFT.&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;/ul&gt;&#xA;&lt;h3 id=&#34;vote-escrow&#34;&gt;Vote Escrow&lt;/h3&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;The &amp;ldquo;ve&amp;rdquo; in &lt;code&gt;vePEG&lt;/code&gt; stands for: vote escrow, which is a mechanism used in decentralized governance to ensure fairness and transparency in decision-making. Any &lt;code&gt;PEG&lt;/code&gt; holder can vote escrow their tokens and receive &lt;code&gt;vePEG&lt;/code&gt; in exchange. With Hyperstable, we call this locking.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>Distribution</title>
